## ðŸ”´ CRITICAL Findings

### 1. `/test_run` â€” Debug Route With NO Authentication (Line 2341)

```python
@app.route("/test_run")
def test_run():
    script_id = "e4f8d9b1-2a3b-4c5d-9e6f-7g8h9i0j1k2l"
    ...
```

> [!CAUTION]
> **This route has ZERO authentication.** Any unauthenticated external attacker can trigger script execution on a target agent by visiting `/test_run`. It hardcodes a script ID and queues a `RUN_SCRIPT` command, mutating `SCRIPTS_FILE` on disk. This is a **remote code execution vector** if the script ID exists.

**Recommendation:** Remove this route entirely, or at minimum guard it with `@admin_required`.

---

### 2. `/api/agent/register` â€” Unauthenticated Agent Registration (Line 1790)

```python
@app.route("/api/agent/register", methods=["POST"])
def agent_register():
```

> [!CAUTION]
> **Any anonymous network client can register a new agent** by sending a POST with an `agent_id` and `hostname`. A newly registered agent receives a valid `token`, which then grants full access to `/api/agent/heartbeat`, `/api/agent/script-event`, and `/api/agent/script-status`. This means an attacker can:
> 1. Register a rogue agent
> 2. Use the returned token to inject fake script status events, create alerts, and pollute execution data
> 3. If a device_key or hostname match is found, **hijack an existing agent's token** (line 1857-1861)

**Recommendation:** Require a shared pre-registration secret, API key, or `@admin_required` approval flow. At minimum, add rate limiting and a registration secret/passphrase.

---

### 3. `/api/auth/presence/inactive` â€” Unauthenticated Session Manipulation (Line 1781)

```python
@app.route("/api/auth/presence/inactive", methods=["POST"])
def api_presence_inactive():
    clear_web_presence()
    return ("", 204)
```

> [!CAUTION]
> **No authentication guard at all.** While it only calls `clear_web_presence()` which operates on the caller's session cookie, the lack of any decorator means:
> - It bypasses all session expiry checks
> - It bypasses the account-active and organization-active checks
> - It can be called by disabled/suspended users
> - A crafted request from a session that was force-logged-out can still hit this endpoint

**Recommendation:** Add `@login_required` decorator.

